urls.description: Wednesday, May 3, 2023 - Public Meeting: City of Kawartha Lakes presents Heritage Inventory Project Public Meeting beginning at 7 p.m. at Coronation Hall (1 King St. West, Omemee, K0L 2W0). The City of Kawartha Lakes is undertaking a multi-year project to create a comprehensive inventory of its historic places, buildings, and landscapes. The Heritage Inventory Project is expanding to Omemee and Fenelon Falls in summer 2023 and the city will be holding public meetings in both communities on May 3 and May 11 to launch the project and provide information and opportunities for participation to community members. A public meeting will also be held in Bobcaygeon on May 8 to follow up on the field work that took place in 2022 and to discuss next steps. Cost: Free. For more information visit https://www.kawarthalakes.ca/en/news/public-meetings-in-may-for-the-heritage-inventory-project.aspx.
